&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the day-to-day procurement lifecycle, including material planning, generating Requests for Quotation (RFQs), creating Purchase Orders (POs), and tracking orders through fulfillment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate directly with production and engineering teams to forecast material needs and ensure timely material availability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up with vendors and resolve all routine vendor and supply chain issues (e.g., delays, shipping errors).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Receiving Operations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the intake process, including inspecting all incoming shipments for accuracy, quality, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify and document material receipt, ensuring all associated paperwork is accurate and complete.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and resolve discrepancies or issues with vendors promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain absolute accuracy in inventory records using inventory management software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and lead regular cycle counts and full inventory audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategically organize and manage warehouse storage to maximize efficiency and accessibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalent; additional certifications in logistics or inventory management are a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in logistics, material handling, or inventory management roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with inventory management software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and accuracy in record-keeping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow and enforce SOPs consistently.&lt;/li&gt;
